ized participation in tradition's sustention and evolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEducationxChinaxChina. 0aEducationzChina. 0aPhilosophy, Confucian. 0aRitualxChina. 0aRitualzChina. 0aTradition (Philosophy). 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Confucianism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845442940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454429/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles